::'''Guangjin:''' (Trailblazer), do you have time to chat now?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Is there anything I can do for you?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202066003-->
::'''Guangjin:''' Based on the investigation of the Realm-Keeping Commission, a few citizens have found a strange phenomenon similar to cloudhymn magic in the Alchemy Commission and Scalegorge Waterscape, and even encountered invisible monsters inside these mirages.
::'''Guangjin:''' According to the statements of the witnesses, we have come to several conclusions regarding the incident: "The phenomenon and the monsters appeared simultaneously. When the mirage was gone, so did the food brought by the starskiff."
::'''Guangjin:''' As the phenomenon is similar to Vidyadhara cloudhymn magic, the orderlies can use echoes to detect the location of the invisible monsters in the area. The exact principles behind this are not yet known.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_202060302_15-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_202060302_15-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} The part about food is really concerning...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202066007-->
:::'''Guangjin:''' Indeed. It's hard to imagine that food is the reason of the phenomenon's appearance.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} How did the monsters appear?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202066009-->
:::'''Guangjin:''' There are always monsters around where cloudhymn magic appears. We have no clue about the reason.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Let's look into it now!
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202066011-->
:::'''Guangjin:''' Please come with me. I'll take you to the scene where the invisible monsters were found.
::<pre>{
